Members of the Wales Assembly do not want to “like the Muppets”
Among some members of the National Assembly is growing dissatisfaction with the proposal to adopt for their name the abbreviation MWP (Member of the Welsh Parliament).
The problematic solution is related to the plans to change the name of the Assembly to the Parliament of Wales.
Members of the Assembly from different political parties are concerned about possible jokes with this abbreviation.
One Labour official, expressing his party’s opinion, expressed concern that the new abbreviation “rhyms Twp and Pwp”.
For our readers not from Wales: in Welsh twp means "stupid", and pwp - "kakashka".
According to a member of the Assembly from the Party of Wales, his organization as a whole “remained dissatisfied” and proposed other options.
Representatives of the conservative party “do not object” to the new abbreviation, but note that the MWP is close to the word Muppet (muppet).
In this context, the letter w in Welsh is pronounced roughly as the letter u in the Yorkshire dialect of English.
The Assembly Committee, which is currently developing a draft law on the name change, made the following statement: “The final decision on the name of the Assembly Members will, of course, remain with them.”
Under the 2017 Welsh Governance Act, the National Assembly of Wales is empowered to change its name.
In June, the Committee published the results of a public opinion poll on the proposed options, according to which the option “Parliament of Wales” instead of “Assembly” found widespread support among the local population.
As for the name of the members of the Assembly, the Committee preferred the Welsh Parliament Members (WMP) option, while the MWP option received the greatest public support.
Apparently, members of the Assembly offer other options, but the Presiding Member, Elin Jones, will not be easy to find a satisfactory solution. Recall that the draft law on amendments should be submitted in a few weeks.
The reform laws will include other modifications to the Assembly ' s work process, including new rules on disqualification of Assembly members and the organization of the Committee ' s system.
Members of the Assembly will vote on the final version of their name during the debate on the bill.
